<h2>
    <a href="/blog/quadtree-1-background/">Quadtrees #1: Background</a>
</h2>




<h6 class="post-meta">
    Posted by:
    
    <a href="/blog/author/christian/">christian</a>
    
    
    
    
    on 15 Nov 2019
</h6>







<p>The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quadtree">quadtree</a> data structure is a convenient way to store the location of arbitrarily-distributed points in two-dimensional space. Quadtrees are often used in image processing and collision detection.</p>




